      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Smaaug</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Well here is my list, its just a couple ideas:</P><P>No upgrade spells:</P><P>Banshee Aura<BR>Feign Death<BR>Shadow Vortex<BR>Screaming Terror<BR>Grim Aura</P><P>These spells could all benefit from an upgrade.  Banshee Aura, and Grim Aura could both use a targeted version, an upgrade version, and a targeted upgrade version ideally.  Death Peace should be given also to Necro class as no other Hybrid get a skill that is more powerful than the parent classes.  Screaming Terror should have an upgrade version and possibly an AoE upgrade version.  Necromancers would be sought after much more if they had the ability to do Crowd control as good as a Bard, and have several of these other buffs.  We would then become an acceptable substitute in level 50 plus encounters.</P><P><BR>No Real Upgrades:</P><P>Post 50 Pet – Hit points/damage should be increased some.  Really they are fine in Fear kiting situations but when your inside a dungeon where fear kiting isn’t an option, they are lacking in that area.  Perhaps a stronger pet that can only be cast indoors would be an idea, or a pet buff that would increase Pet hitpoints and damage output that is only castable indoors.  Also at high end lvls, pets don’t seem to be really an upgrade.  Testing this myself, between the 49 and 59 pet, the only difference seemed to be the 55 Augment spell.  The Spec pet won by a fourth of a yellow bubble.  </P><P><BR>Darkness line.  Majority of the Necromancers I know use the lower level Dooming Darkness as their primary snare type spell.  Reason for this is, in group situations snare has to be done quick, if its slowed 10 seconds later than it arrived, then it will already be half dead.  Make the high level snare/darkness spells the same cast time as dooming darkness.  This will make them useful., and make us a clear alternative to other snaring classes.    </P><P>Veil of Xarn – I am not this high yet but from my research, this spell does pretty much the same thing as harmshield and is night time only.  </P><P>There are some others I cant think of at the time, where they are underused due to their long cast times or high resistivity. </P><P><BR>Spell Availabilty – As has been posted before.  Spells that would help out a lot are dropping from super high level MoBs or are so rare as to be considered not in the game.  </P><P>Spells that are Lacking:</P><P>Mind Wrack – 300 mana for 600 mana?  And you loose 100 of that mana if you have 2 tanks in the group.  The amount of the mana returned should  be increased.  With 4 people in the group that might possibly need mana, and those getting 50 mana each.  That gives us 200 mana at a cost of 600mana.  That is basically the same unefficient twitch that we have now, in group form.  Increase the mana return and only give it to the casters in the group..  Also make sure the mana is diverted to another person if the person is full mana.  For a spell that costs 600 mana, it should give 100 mana each to each caster in the group and have a 10 second refresh time.  That would make us sought after in situations where an enchanter cant be found.  With both the upgrade to Screaming Terror and a way to increase mana regen at a decent level for the casters in the group, we then could do the job of the enchanter in group situations (not in high level raid encounters)</P><P>Group Buff Tap spells – Basically they are a little low on the amount they add in my opinion.  I think they should be increased by about 10 percent, at least.</P><P>Essence Emerald Spells – Remove the component please.  With the exception of the rez spell.  Either do this, or make an alternative to getting the component.</P><P>Wishlist:</P><P>Pets - Give us a few options on pets.  I have always liked the idea that different bonechips pull different pets (ie barbed chips for barbed skeletons).  </P><P>Pet commands - give us a few more control commands.  Taking the /pet hold one and making it a basic command would be a good start.  I would also like the idea of a /pet range ## (sets pet wandering range from the caster, will not chase or wander beyond this distance).  This would basically allow a caster the ability to wander a bad pathing area without worry of a pet going the long way through a dungeon or ignoring the casters /pet back off command and chasing a MoB into a room of many MoBs.  Also this will reduce the chance of a pet going after Mezzed targets.  Overall this will increase the demand on pet classes in total for raid situations.  Most Raids wont allow pets since they often break mez and wander off and agro other MoBs.  </P><P>Epic - Number one the look.  A staff with a spinning burning skull on the end of it or something like that would look nice.  Perhaps then we would get out of the EQ comic section when it came to our epic.  Secondly the effect.  Basically this is our lvl 49 snare with 100 more damaging DoT.  That is all well and good, but the cast time is the same.  Those who use it still have to load a snare back up, else they will never be able to get the effect spell off.  Here is a couple of ideas for an effect:</P><P>Summon Essence Emerald:  kill 2 birds with one stone<BR>High end Lifetap:  Like 1k hps<BR>Lich:  Make the bearer constantly be in lich form, but with a downgraded hp per tick.  Something like 5 hp for 20 mana.  <BR>Summon Corpse:  manaless componentless instant cast corpse summon<BR>Super pet;  Been done with the mages, very useful with them.  Different model and with a strong lifetap.<BR>Swiss Army DoT:  roll all the necro type DoTs into one, Disease, Fire, Cold, Poison, Magic.  Make each one do 300dmg in 30 seconds.  That would be a total of 1500dmg in 30 seconds.  Make them all stack, but also make it so that if one or two is resisted the whole DoT is not resisted.  <BR>Group Super helper:  Make it have a group spell on it, that has DMF, a version of lich, Grim Aura and Banshee Aura in it.  That will make a epic Necro sought after heavily in a group.  <BR>Group Lifetap spell - say 200 per member for 1200dmg.  15 second recast time, and a 8 second cast time.  <BR>Group Feign Death -  self explanatory</P><P>Heres a new one for you too. <BR>Engulfing Shadows - When clicked produces an AoE short duration Blindness spell, on a rather large radius (lure).  Then followed by a 9 second AoE lure type Screaming Terror (mez and stun) spell.  Finish it up with a a group Levant spell, or group Gather Shadows/Invis vs Undead mix spell.  Basically the necro produces a cloud of shadows, blinding everyone including the MoBs.  While everything cant see, all the Mobs are stunned and memory wiped.  Then some kind of escape spell is applied.  When the cloud clears, the group is either all invisible or at the zone in.  </P><P>Lich based on race - Iksar skeletons for Iksar necromancers, Dwarf Skeletons for gnomes and halfing.  Regular skeletons for Erudites, Dark Elfs, etc</P><P>Grim Horses - Perfably questable instead of buyable.  But make the highest end horse in a skeleton version.  This will be great for Necros, and Shadow Knights.  Would look great to see a dark Knight riding around on a horse covered in leather but nothing but a skeleton under neath</P><P></P><P></P><P></P><P></P><P></P><P></P><P><BR>Smaaug Darqsmoke<BR>Iksar Necromancer<BR>Brell Serilis</font></td>
      </tr>
